427
00:40:59,403 --> 00:41:08,612
So then everything else begins to collapse, but only collapse in the sense of supporting the delusion, of supporting those habits which are unwholesome.

428
00:41:09,333 --> 00:41:09,672
Okay?

429
00:41:12,251 --> 00:41:21,365
And as we pointed out, the other escape is between the vedana, the feeling, and the reaction of tanha.

430
00:41:22,788 --> 00:41:24,550
So that's when we are renouncing.

431
00:41:24,570 --> 00:41:28,516
So the whole of the spiritual life is a process of renunciation.

432
00:41:28,536 --> 00:41:30,199
Right, let go, let go.

433
00:41:30,219 --> 00:41:37,168
Now, at first, when you begin to renounce something, you might feel you've lost something.

434
00:41:37,469 --> 00:41:38,952
I mean, have you noticed that?

435
00:41:40,315 --> 00:41:48,063
If you don't react to the greed while you're eating, you can try this when, for instance, you prepare yourself something that you really like.

436
00:41:50,186 --> 00:41:56,474
And you're maintaining a distance and you're just tasting pleasant sensations.

437
00:41:57,396 --> 00:42:02,041
Now, because you're not indulging, there's a level of excitement disappears.

438
00:42:03,802 --> 00:42:06,947
And you're not enjoying the food as much as you did before.

439
00:42:08,563 --> 00:42:10,085
And you think, oh, there's something wrong with this.

440
00:42:11,027 --> 00:42:14,652
I've got to get back to stuffing myself.

441
00:42:14,672 --> 00:42:27,969
But I'm hoping that the talk you heard this morning has convinced you that there's a penalty to pay for that excitement, which is, of course, the frustration, the anger, the anxiety, etc., etc.

442
00:42:28,731 --> 00:42:38,284
So you have to let go of something in order to begin to experience pure enjoyment without the suffering.

443
00:42:39,394 --> 00:42:44,427
And that's what's so difficult because we just love to indulge.

444
00:42:45,108 --> 00:42:46,331
It gives us that little buzz.

445
00:42:46,873 --> 00:42:50,603
And of course, the whole consumer society is based upon that.

446
00:42:50,735 --> 00:42:53,918
It's not based upon you being pleasantly happy.

447
00:42:53,998 --> 00:42:55,619
It's based upon you being excited.

448
00:42:56,059 --> 00:42:57,400
That's why these products change.

449
00:42:57,481 --> 00:43:03,407
Even if they only change the look of a mobile, they'll change in order to make you excited.

450
00:43:03,726 --> 00:43:06,009
So that, oh yeah, I've got to get that one.

451
00:43:06,028 --> 00:43:12,195
So the whole consumer process is driven by that desire for excitement, not happiness.

452
00:43:12,875 --> 00:43:16,237
Because when happiness comes, there also comes contentment.

453
00:43:16,898 --> 00:43:17,900
You are contented.

454
00:43:18,400 --> 00:43:20,202
So you're not chasing things at all.

455
00:43:20,181 --> 00:43:23,646
And that happiness is coming from within you, not because of an object.

456
00:43:24,989 --> 00:43:35,344
Now that's a hard thing for us to move towards because it does feel you're losing something in not allowing yourself to indulge.

457
00:43:39,271 --> 00:43:40,333
So...

458
00:43:43,603 --> 00:43:57,304
And yes, just the final thing, every time, remember, you renounce that indulgence, even if it's only a little bit, you know, even if it's just, you normally have three or four biscuits and you just say, well, I'm only going to have two.

459
00:43:58,347 --> 00:44:04,356
See, even a little renunciation is undercutting that sense of self, right?

460
00:44:04,376 --> 00:44:08,682
Because it's that delusive self that's creating this wrong desire.

461
00:44:10,603 --> 00:44:26,605
I can only hope my words have been of some assistance, that I have not caused even greater confusion, and that by your devotion to the practice you will be liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

